UPDATING
In addition to maintaining the records that support the PSM / RMP / CalARP documents, Fresh Express is obligated to update these documents in accordance with 40 CFR §68.19O and 19 CCR §5070.11. This includes submitting the modifications in a method and format to the Monterey County Health Department, Environmental Health Bureau. The following items outline the criteria for updating the PSM / RMP / CalARP document.
1.	Within five years of its initial submission or most recent update required by items 2 through 7 (NOTE: Five year update criteria shifts to five years from the revision date if an update is required as per items 2 through 7);
2.	No later than three years after a newly regulated substance is first listed by the California Office of Emergency Services;
3.	No later than the date on which a new regulated substance is first present in an already covered process above a threshold quantity;
4.	No later than the date on which a regulated substance is first present above a threshold quantity in a new process;
5.	Within six months of a change that requires a revised HAZOP or Hazard Review;
6.	Within six months of a change that requires a revised off-site consequence analysis (Hazard Assessment) (i.e. process is moved so as to affect different sensitive receptors, the quantity of the regulated substance is increased, etc.);
7.	Within six months of a change that alters the program level that applied to any covered process (Program 1, 2, or 3).
